this series deserves a continuation!!! Tom Ellis is breathtaking as Dr.  Rush. The progression to redemption and sacrifice is heartwrenching.  While I doubt he could pull off both series (and Lucifer) together, this is something Ellis needs to return to and bring to fruition. Storytelling is that good.

Rush is a brilliant series.

The series circles around dr. Rush, a capable but drug addicted MD who works independently for mostly shady people who pay well. Tom Ellis portrays this character in a believable and sympathetic way and makes the best out of the script. Dr. Rushes flaws and addiction make you want to shake him at times  however there is this other side to him, that brings out the human and fragile aspects. Even though the show runs with the medical topic, I found the idea of a freelancing doctor, bringing it out of the hospital, interesting. Allas the first and only season ends with ONLY cliffhangers for all the main characters and leaves the audience wanting. I think the writers could have rounded it up in a more satisfying way. If you like Tom Ellis and this series: check out his new gig: Lucifer!

Loved this from start to finish! Wish it had a second season to resolve the plot lines left in the air! About five minutes in you totally forget any other character you've seen Tom Ellis portray - which is to me the hallmark of a superb actor.
